The card drop down menu (which normally show actions available : add a comment, create a subtask, ...) is broken on my "french version" of the product due to a Javascript error :
{code}
Erreur : missing ) after argument list
Fichier Source : http://jira.net.holydis.com/secure/VersionBoard.jspa?decorator=none&selectedProjectId=10030
Ligne : 1, Colonne : 46
Code Source :
getIssue('10066','TSQ-601').openMenu('Ajout d'une sous-tâche', 'Commenter', '', '', '', 'Supprimer', 'Whiteboard');
{code}

I received this feature request today:

{quote}
It would be nice to have some "start working" and "stop working" buttons in the planning board that would automate filling in the form for the "time spend" field.
{quote}

Cheers,

Ximon

Unsure of how the data got this way, but several issues have multiple values in the Rank field.  Re-ranking them does not replace the value, but adds an additional one.

Sample error in log:

{noformat:title=atlassian-jira.log}
2008-08-05 12:06:19,269 http-80-Processor13 ERROR [issue.customfields.impl.AbstractSingleFieldType] More than one value stored for custom field id 'customfield_10232' for issue 'CLRT-22694'.  Values [1.5105E11, 1.5105E11]
{noformat}

Have not yet tried re-optimizing the Rank field.  I expect that will fix the issue.  But clearly it is still a problem if it gets this way to begin with and subsequent ranking only compounds the problem.
